                Florus Optati <lb n="2"/><expan><abbr>fil</abbr><ex>ius</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>Sequan</abbr><ex>us</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>an</abbr><ex>norum</ex></expan> L <lb n="3"/><gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/>ia Daphnis <lb n="4"/><supplied reason="lost">u</supplied>xor <expan><abbr>n<am>n</am></abbr><ex>orum</ex></expan> <lb n="5"/><gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/><expan><abbr>XL</abbr><ex cert="low"/>V</expan> <expan><abbr>h</abbr><ex>ic</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>s</abbr><ex>ita</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>e</abbr><ex>st</ex></expan>
            </ab></div>
            <div type="commentary">
                <p>In sekundärer Verwendung in einer spätrömischen Mauer gefunden. Zwei nicht aneinanderpassende Fragmente, z.T. modern rekonstruiert. Über der Inschrift in einer Doppelaedicula Portraitbüsten der Verstorbenen. Z. 5: statt XL(?)V auch XI(?)V möglich. (B): Z. 1: Horus.</p>
            </div>
